The paper deals with algorithms for planar graphs, which are often studied in the computational geometry community (cs.CG). The use of Gomory-Hu trees and minimum cycle basis suggests a focus on graph theory (cs.DM, cs.GT). The problem of finding min $st$-cuts is a classic problem in graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a new algorithmic result, which could potentially be of interest to the theoretical computer science community (cs.CC).
